Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Obscenity laws
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0407bw3
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 20 Feb 1977
How to ensure freedom of speech is maintained while curbing obscene publications. Cooke recalls meeting Mrs Simpson for the first, and last, time. The sound quality on this recording is variable/poor. This archive edition of Letter from America was recorded by one of two listeners, who between them taped and labelled over 650 Letter From America programmes from 1973 to 1989. It was restored by the BBC in 2014. Show less